{"article_id":"KEME09WFDgkLvn1J","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"In the battle for primary votes , Hillary Clinton and Bernie Sanders are locked in a tight battle .","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"But you would n't know it","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"to look at the superdelegates .","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"In the unseen battle for these party insiders , Clinton has an overwhelming lead .","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"Of the 712 Democratic superdelegates , 449","depth":11},{"id":5,"text":"( or about 63 percent )","depth":11},{"id":6,"text":"currently support Clinton ,","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"according to the latest Associated Press survey of superdelegates .","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"Only 19 support Sanders .","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"( AP did not reach 62 superdelegates ,","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"and 182 remained uncommitted or undecided . )","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"Taking superdelegates out ,","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"Sanders has a 36-32 lead among delegates ,","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"based on the vote in Iowa and New Hampshire .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"This superdelegate advantage is not only a huge lead for Clinton ,","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"but a big gain as well .","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"Since the AP 's November survey , her total has jumped 90 delegates .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"Sanders , meanwhile , has risen 11 , from eight to 19 .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"Keep in mind","depth":5},{"id":19,"text":"that Clinton also had a big superdelegate lead the last time","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"she ran ,","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"but went on to lose the nomination .","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"As of January 2008","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"- shortly into the nominating process but still before Super Tuesday -","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"she likewise maintained a huge lead , of 201 to Barack Obama 's 89 and John Edwards ' 40 ,","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"according to the AP .","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"Then , in February 2008 , Obama was starting to quickly pick up superdelegates ,","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"while Clinton had started to lose some to his side .","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"This time around , she is maintaining strong support among the party 's `` establishment '' thus far ,","depth":6},{"id":29,"text":"despite the fact","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"that the race is tight in some primaries and caucuses .","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"Superdelegates consist of some well-known names","depth":4},{"id":32,"text":"- members of Congress and former presidents","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"( Bill Clinton is one ) ,","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"for example -","depth":5},{"id":35,"text":"and many party insiders","depth":5},{"id":36,"text":"whom most Americans do n't know -","depth":5},{"id":37,"text":"state party leaders and Democratic National Committee members , for example .","depth":4},{"id":38,"text":"While the non-superdelegates are allocated","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"based on how people vote in the various state caucuses and primaries ,","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"the superdelegates are `` unbound , ''","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"meaning they can choose whom they want .","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"And thus far , they have overwhelmingly chosen Clinton .","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"This can make for delegate counts","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"that do n't quite seem to make sense","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"considering vote totals .","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"In New Hampshire ,","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"where Sanders won the primary by a 22-point margin ,","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"both he and Clinton have 15 total delegates .","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"While he won 15 of the state 's 24 non-superdelegates ,","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"she has six of the eight superdelegates in her corner .","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"Some Sanders supporters ,","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"upset about this system ,","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"have taken to contacting superdelegates ,","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"as the AP reports .","depth":5},{"id":55,"text":"And one MoveOn.org petition ,","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"declaring","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"that `` race for the Democratic Party nomination should be decided by who gets the most votes ,","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"and not who has the most support from party insiders , ''","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"asks superdelegates to `` pledge to back the will of the voters . ''","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"Currently , that petition has more than 161,000 signatures .","depth":5},{"id":61,"text":"The fact","depth":6},{"id":62,"text":"that the superdelegate system gives the party outsize influence","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"clearly upsets many Sanders supporters ,","depth":5},{"id":64,"text":"but giving the party outsize influence is the point of the system .","depth":4},{"id":65,"text":"Superdelegates were created in 1982","depth":5},{"id":66,"text":"to `` improve the party 's mainstream appeal ''","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"by giving party insiders more influence","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"and reduce that of `` activists , ''","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"as Brookings Institution 's Thomas Mann and AEI 's Norman Ornstein wrote in 2008 ,","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"when Clinton and Obama were also battling it out for superdelegates .","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"Ornstein and Mann laid out several arguments for the superdelegate system :","depth":6},{"id":72,"text":"It 's a sort of `` peer review ''","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"to choose the most electable candidate ,","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"they wrote ,","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"and promotes a sense of unity ,","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"making `` stronger ties between the party and its elected officials . ''","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"Of course , in a tight race , that `` unity '' argument is probably hard to see from a voter 's perspective .","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"And that 's not lost on superdelegates .","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"One","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"- then-Sen. John Kerry -","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"told the New York Times in 2008","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"that he feared the repercussions","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"of choosing a nominee","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"that went against the will of the voters .","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"`` My personal opinion is it would be a mistake and disastrous either way for the superdelegates","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"- insiders , establishment politicians -","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"to come along and overturn the expressed view of those pledged delegates , ''","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"he said .","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"Indeed , many superdelegates have to be re-elected themselves at some point ,","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"Ornstein and Mann point out .","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"Going too sharply against voters ' wishes is n't going to do them any good in that sense .","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"But then , superdelegates remain unbound ,","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"even if they 've chosen a candidate already .","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"Should the race swing heavily in Sanders ' favor ,","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"some superdelegates","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"who are currently backing Clinton","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"could always switch their support .","depth":12}],"relations":[{"parent":195,"left":135,"right":194,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":135,"left":128,"right":134,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":115,"right":127,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":115,"left":0,"right":114,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":114,"left":107,"right":113,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":107,"left":99,"right":106,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":99,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":106,"left":3,"right":10